ENTRY       EC 2.4.2.56                 Enzyme
NAME        kaempferol 3-O-xylosyltransferase;
            F3XT;
            UDP-D-xylose:flavonol 3-O-xylosyltransferase;
            flavonol 3-O-xylosyltransferase
CLASS       Transferases;
            Glycosyltransferases;
            Pentosyltransferases
SYSNAME     UDP-alpha-D-xylose:kaempferol 3-O-D-xylosyltransferase
REACTION    UDP-alpha-D-xylose + kaempferol = UDP + kaempferol 3-O-beta-D-xyloside [RN:R10609]
ALL_REAC    R10609
SUBSTRATE   UDP-alpha-D-xylose [CPD:C00190];
            kaempferol [CPD:C05903]
PRODUCT     UDP [CPD:C00015];
            kaempferol 3-O-beta-D-xyloside [CPD:C20727]
COMMENT     The enzyme from the plant Euonymus alatus also catalyses the 3-O-D-xylosylation of other flavonols (e.g. quercetin, isorhamnetin, rhamnetin, myricetin, fisetin) with lower activity.
HISTORY     EC 2.4.2.56 created 2013
